    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes a backward-compatible technique that may be used by OSPF (Open Shortest Path First) implementations to advertise a router's unavailability to forward transit traffic or to lower the preference level for the paths through such a router.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This document obsoletes RFC 3137.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
